<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1698,2024]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1885,1911]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[333,502,1886,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matricarius">
<emphasis box="[333,502,1886,1911]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">E. matricarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from congeners in 
<collectingCountry box="[871,918,1886,1912]" name="Iran" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Iran</collectingCountry>
by the combination of following characters: Occiput yellow laterally; mesonotum with brown or blackish brown pattern, prescutellar area and sctuellum yellow; second flagellomere much shorter than first flagellomere; invagination of reservoir shallow and furca without sclerotisation around genital orifice.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198248/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" targetBox="[177,1417,193,1913]" targetPageId="11">
